Oh hi Laura :)
as a fan of arachnids, and a macro-photographer, really enjoyed your Q&A, raised black widows for a time had 3 generations, continually fascinated with all species,  but leaning toward jumpers,

Hard working only brings interesting scenes we view here. Well studied contents are of special interest.
2 points draw my attention. Firstly, failed attempts by ambush predators. Many other documentaries tend to focus on their success story, but here that's not always the case. Missing a prey, teased by false alarm.. Surprisingly their sensor/skill doesn't appear sophisticated very much. Unexpected face of nature captured.
Secondly, spiders' memory issue is an intriguing subject. This is very inspiring! Plenty to ask to experts. Hunch is there may be simpler explanations how to reach prey caches rather than relying on memory. How to make much of past catches remains to be presented!
